    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-12T17:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-12T17:30:00-05:00" n="322"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.6176/32: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stewart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-12T18:30:00-04:00"
                            >October 12, 1943—6:30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–582. Embassy’s despatch No. 1536, September 23. The limitations on the
                    operations of the Honduran and Nicaraguan organizations and contractors of
                    Rubber Development Corporation, as outlined in the despatch, meet with the
                    Department’s full approval. The Washington office of the Corporation has also
                    expressed to the Department its approval.</p>
                <p>The solution is of course to be considered as a scheme of procurement operations
                    only, and not as an indication of any opinion on or recognition of border claims
                    by any Government.</p>
                <p>Sent to Managua and to Tegucigalpa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
